rld War, Germany no longer enjoyed the trust of other nations. What did West Germany do to rebuild confidence? What was the role of trust, mistrust, and supervision during the East-West conflict as West Germany was integrated into the Western alliance, and how did they affect international relations between the two blocs? This study examines personal ties, rhetorical strategies, and institutional connections.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aWorld politicsy20th century. 4aAußenpolitik. 4aDeutschland. 4aDiplomatiegeschichte. 4aInternationale Beziehungen. 4aOst-West-Konflikt. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aEast-Western conflict.  aForeign policy.  aGermany.1 aReinfeldt, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGotto, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKreis, Reinhild, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPeter, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiß, Peter Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGassert, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKreis, Reinhild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLappenküper, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2014z9783110370225oZDB-23-DEG0